 First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Estmond de Mercia was born about 1067, in Bristol, England, United Kingdom, his father, Eadnoth the Constable, was 34 and his mother, Rissa de Dursley, was 34. He married Lady Godiva Of Normandy in 1098, in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died about 1142, in his hometown, at the age of 77."},"et":{"about 1067–about 1142":"umbes 1067–umbes 1142","1060–1125":"1060–1125","1067–1142":"1067–1142","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1099–1168":"1099–1168","1035–1068":"1035–1068","1035–1069":"1035–1069","1099":"1099","1098":"1098","1142":"1142","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","1048":"1048","1125":"1125","1069":"1069","1168":"1168","1068":"1068","1035":"1035","Abt 1099":"umbes 1099","1067":"1067","about 1067":"umbes 1067","about 1142":"umbes 1142","Dursley, Gloucestershire, England":"Dursley, Gloucestershire, England","Gloucestershire, Anglo-Saxon England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bristol, Gloucestershire, Anglo-Saxon England":"Bristol, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bleadon, Somerset, England":"Bleadon, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Berkeley, Gloucestershire, England":"Berkeley, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1067–about 1142":"noin 1067–noin 1142","1060–1125":"1060–1125","1067–1142":"1067–1142","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1099–1168":"1099–1168","1035–1068":"1035–1068","1035–1069":"1035–1069","1099":"1099","1098":"1098","1142":"1142","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","1048":"1048","1125":"1125","1069":"1069","1168":"1168","1068":"1068","1035":"1035","Abt 1099":"noin 1099","1067":"1067","about 1067":"noin 1067","about 1142